% Failed :assign by precondition (5) scope/pattern (BETA spec section 3.2.2).
% In `?- X = X.` the query's X is a polymorphic logic variable
% (X : ?t4), so `:assign ?X := [].` survives the precondition (3)
% type check (the RHS unifies with the polymorphic LHS). It then
% fails the runtime-side scope check inside `cmdAssign`: the
% type-meta-variable ?TV_n introduced when the RHS `[]` was typed
% as `list ?t` escapes the scope of X, so the snapshot is restored
% and the error "*** :assign error: scope violation for 'X' --
% out-of-scope: ?TV_n" is reported.
type p (nat -> o).
